  "dct:title": "How to define workflows",
  "dct:description": "This documentation introduces the abstract schema used in NOMAD to define, document, and visualize workflows. A workflow describes how data was generated by linking input and output data through tasks. The guide explains how to structure workflow metadata using YAML, including nested workflows and cross-entry references via TaskReference. It also shows how to extend base workflows with custom fields and how workflows are visualized in the NOMAD GUI using the interactive graph tool. These capabilities support clear data provenance and traceable scientific processes.",
